INSTRUCTION TO RUN LOCALLY
--------------------------
Requirements browser, active internet connection and nodejs installed on your machine

1. Uncompress the file
2. Change your directory to the folder that contains the code
3. Now install the required packages by using
	sudo npm install
4. Now run the server by using the following command
	node app.js
   The server is now started on port 3978
5. Now go to the browser and go to the following url localhost:3978
6. The bot is now running locally and can be tested now.

Make sure that bot can connect to LUIS. LUIS endpoint URL is specified in .env file 
